\f0\b\fs26 \cf2 \cb3 Reflection paper on The Medium Is The Message\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj

\b0 \cf2 \
When I first read 'The Medium Is the Message' I remember it being quite strange and I couldn't completely realize the purpose of it. But once we started our project 'Mu', I realized how much each and every stage of the work is important for conveying the message. We started off with trying to find a perfect material, a perfect location and a perfect form shape for our project. Initially, yes, I was slightly confused as to how it is important. But once we set off, I realized the effect of using cardboard instead of lanterns, the effect of an indoor wall as opposed to the open space that we used, etc. It's not just the content that affects what you perceive or feel; the medium used to convey is also extremely important. In our case, I think more than the content, the message of pure nothingness was conveyed through the medium of lanterns, structures and the open and natural space. Similarly we used the medium of sound and sight to add profound depth and understanding to our concept. As mentioned in the reading, people seldom notice the influence of the medium. The case provided about the electric bulb and light was quite impressive according to me. It was exactly the sort of thing most of us would never have noticed before. Personally, I think it is a talent to distinguish the effects of medium from that of the content in putting across a message. In fact, I was exceptionally happy when I was able to analyze and realize how much one is deceived into thinking that content is the only messenger of meaning.\
