\b Reflection paper on New Media From Borges to HTML
\b0 \
\
Lev Manovich's scrutiny of the new and growing relationship between art and technology in "New Media from Borges to HTML" is quite interesting and enlightening. Art has generally been associated with paper, craft work, canvas and the like. However the new media, electronic media, has widely disseminated \'a0its way through the field of art. It took quite some time to grow into the phenomenon it is today. However, it has become a creator, safe keeper, transporter, converter, displayer and much more for art. Just like how our project's foundations have mostly been in the digital world (Processing, VPT, Video encoders, etc.) the nature of art has almost completely and fundamentally changed. The only concern of this development is that, just like how new "poets" appear every day through blogs, irrespective of their ability, "artists" will also start appearing every other second in different parts of the world through the world wide web and this can result in a general fall in standard of what is perceived as art.\'a0\
For eg: One key aspect in our project was transcoding, which we used for converting from one form of output (code output) to the other (video) during projection.\'a0\
